cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.IR. 

The paper proposes a novel descriptor for dealing with affine distortions induced by viewpoint changes in computer vision applications. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also uses PCA for dimensionality reduction, which is a common technique in machine learning and falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper uses a subspace assumption, which is a common technique in linear algebra and optimization, and could fall under the category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also evaluates its proposed method on various datasets, which could fall under the categories of cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
